<subSubSection id="C323A580FFC71813FF22D2E76AF0CB74" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B86F60BFFC71813FF22D2E76AF0CB74" blockId="60.[151,1437,1230,1794]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
The taxonomic situation of 
<taxonomicName id="4C398D88FFC71813FE62D2E7687BC890" authorityName="Van Damme, Sinev &amp; Dumont" authorityYear="2011" box="[471,588,1230,1254]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Chydoridae" genus="Anthalona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="B94D2A19FFC71813FE62D2E7687BC890" box="[471,588,1230,1254]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Anthalona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94D2A19FFC71813FDE0D2E66891C891" bold="true" box="[597,678,1231,1255]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27E9762FFC71813FDE0D2E66891C891" box="[597,678,1231,1255]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
remains complex. 
<taxonomicName id="4C398D88FFC71813FC31D2E76E3EC890" box="[900,1033,1230,1254]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Chydoridae" genus="Anthalona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineolata">
<emphasis id="B94D2A19FFC71813FC31D2E76E3EC890" box="[900,1033,1230,1254]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">A. lineolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F32EB69BFFC71813FBE6D2E76EA1C890" box="[1107,1174,1230,1254]" name="China" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C398D88FFC71813FB67D2E76FABC890" baseAuthorityName="Brehm" baseAuthorityYear="1933" box="[1234,1436,1230,1254]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Alona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alonopsiformis">
<emphasis id="B94D2A19FFC71813FB67D2E76FABC890" box="[1234,1436,1230,1254]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">A. alonopsiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingCountry id="F32EB69BFFC71813FF4BD2DB6B4BC97C" box="[254,380,1266,1290]" name="Philippines" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Philippines</collectingCountry>
still need evaluation. We currently count seven species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C398D88FFC71813FBBAD2DA6EB4C97D" authorityName="Van Damme, Sinev &amp; Dumont" authorityYear="2011" box="[1039,1155,1267,1291]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Chydoridae" genus="Anthalona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94D2A19FFC71813FBBAD2DA6EB4C97D" box="[1039,1155,1267,1291]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Anthalona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the genus will grow larger. Records of 
<taxonomicName id="4C398D88FFC71813FEDFD33F6BE9C958" authorityName="Van Damme, Sinev &amp; Dumont" authorityYear="2011" box="[362,478,1302,1326]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Chydoridae" genus="Anthalona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94D2A19FFC71813FEDFD33F6BE9C958" box="[362,478,1302,1326]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Anthalona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appear as 
<taxonomicName id="4C398D88FFC71813FDEFD33F6922C958" authorityName="Sars, 1901 sensu Sars" authorityYear="1901" box="[602,789,1302,1326]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Alona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verrucosa">
<emphasis id="B94D2A19FFC71813FDEFD33F6922C958" box="[602,789,1302,1326]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Alona verrucosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in literature worldwide and more research of East Asian (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA88BFAFFC71813FF62D313682EC924" author="Rajapaksa &amp; Fernando" box="[215,537,1338,1362]" firstAuthor="Rajapaksa" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="49 - 69" refId="ref40517" refString="Rajapaksa, R. &amp; Fernando, C. H. (1982) The Cladocera of Sri Lanka (Ceylon), with remarks on some species. Hydrobiologia, 94, 49 - 69." type="journal article" year="1982">Rajapaksa &amp; Fernando 1982</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA88BFAFFC71813FD91D3126948C924" author="Dumont &amp; Van De Velde" box="[548,895,1338,1362]" firstAuthor="Dumont" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="55 - 65" refId="ref39672" refString="Dumont, H. J. &amp; Van De Velde, I. (1977) Report on a collection of Cladocera and Copepoda from Nepal. Hydrobiologia, 53, 55 - 65." type="journal article" year="1977">Dumont &amp; Van De Velde 1977</bibRefCitation>
), Australian and African 
<taxonomicName id="4C398D88FFC71813FB2ED3126F38C925" authorityName="Van Damme, Sinev &amp; Dumont" authorityYear="2011" box="[1179,1295,1339,1363]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Chydoridae" genus="Anthalona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94D2A19FFC71813FB2ED3126F38C925" box="[1179,1295,1339,1363]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Anthalona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are likely to reveal additional species. In particular, status of Australian and South East Asian populations should be examined further; we did not study these regions sufficiently although the 
<taxonomicName id="4C398D88FFC71813FCD4D3AA69D8C9EC" authorityName="Sars, 1901 sensu Sars" authorityYear="1901" box="[865,1007,1411,1435]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Alona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verrucosa">
<emphasis id="B94D2A19FFC71813FCD4D3AA69D8C9EC" box="[865,1007,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">A. verrucosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group is common here and there is no name available for the Australian populations, which may well be different from 
<taxonomicName id="4C398D88FFC71813FB9CD38F6EA3C9C8" authorityName="Van Damme, Sinev &amp; Dumont" authorityYear="2011" box="[1065,1172,1446,1470]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Chydoridae" genus="Anthalona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusa" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B94D2A19FFC71813FB9CD38F6EA3C9C8" box="[1065,1172,1446,1470]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">A. obtusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94D2A19FFC71813FB2ED38E6EEDC9C9" bold="true" box="[1179,1242,1447,1471]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27E9762FFC71813FB2ED38E6EEDC9C9" box="[1179,1242,1447,1471]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(or more species may be present). We did encounter more new species that were not incorporated in this study. Brief examination of specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="F32EB69BFFC71813FEE0D3C76BADCA70" box="[341,410,1518,1542]" name="Nepal" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, samples of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA88BFAFFC71813FD99D3C66995CA70" author="Dumont &amp; Van De Velde" box="[556,930,1518,1542]" firstAuthor="Dumont" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="55 - 65" refId="ref39672" refString="Dumont, H. J. &amp; Van De Velde, I. (1977) Report on a collection of Cladocera and Copepoda from Nepal. Hydrobiologia, 53, 55 - 65." type="journal article" year="1977">Dumont &amp; Van De Velde (1977)</bibRefCitation>
for example, showed that these populations cannot be assigned to any of the species described herein. Furthermore, during finalization of this manuscript, we encountered two clearly different, unnamed species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C398D88FFC71813FC96D01F69A0CA38" authorityName="Van Damme, Sinev &amp; Dumont" authorityYear="2011" box="[803,919,1590,1614]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Chydoridae" genus="Anthalona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94D2A19FFC71813FC96D01F69A0CA38" box="[803,919,1590,1614]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Anthalona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, one from 
<collectingCountry id="F32EB69BFFC71813FB96D01F6EB0CA38" box="[1059,1159,1590,1614]" name="Thailand" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(Sinev, pers. obs.) and another from 
<collectingCountry id="F32EB69BFFC71813FE9AD0736B43CA04" box="[303,372,1626,1650]" name="Brazil" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(from Amazon; A. Ghidini, pers. obs.). So, even in South America, new findings should not be surprising. 
<taxonomicName id="4C398D88FFC71813FEA0D0576BBDCAE0" authorityName="Van Damme, Sinev &amp; Dumont" authorityYear="2011" box="[277,394,1662,1686]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Chydoridae" genus="Anthalona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="B94D2A19FFC71813FEA0D0576BBDCAE0" box="[277,394,1662,1686]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Anthalona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94D2A19FFC71813FE24D0566BE8CAE1" bold="true" box="[401,479,1663,1687]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27E9762FFC71813FE24D0566BE8CAE1" box="[401,479,1663,1687]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is therefore more speciose than presented here. More data on ecology should also be gathered; in particular sympatry of the Neotropical species 
<taxonomicName id="4C398D88FFC71813FC8ED08A69AECACC" authorityName="Van Damme, Sinev &amp; Dumont" authorityYear="2011" box="[827,921,1699,1723]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Chydoridae" genus="Anthalona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acuta">
<emphasis id="B94D2A19FFC71813FC8ED08A69AECACC" box="[827,921,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">A. acuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C398D88FFC71813FC66D08A6E53CACC" authorityName="Sars, 1901 sensu Sars" authorityYear="1901" box="[979,1124,1699,1723]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Alona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verrucosa">
<emphasis id="B94D2A19FFC71813FC66D08A6E53CACC" box="[979,1124,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">A. verrucosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(and even 
<taxonomicName id="4C398D88FFC71813FB51D08A6F40CACD" baseAuthorityName="Sinev &amp; Hollwedel" baseAuthorityYear="2002" box="[1252,1399,1699,1723]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Chydoridae" genus="Anthalona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brandorffi">
<emphasis id="B94D2A19FFC71813FB51D08A6F40CACD" box="[1252,1399,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">A. brandorffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is interesting, to study niche separation of sympatric chydorids in a single small pool with externally different characters.
</paragraph>
